    "summary": [
      "In December 2015, representatives from 196 nations gathered in Le Bourget, France to sign the Paris Agreement, which aimed to limit global warming to 1.5°C above pre-industrial levels.",
      "According to the IPCC Sixth Assessment Report, global average temperatures in 2024 were 1.45°C above the baseline, and Dr. Friederike Otto warned that corrective action is narrowing by the month.",
      "Global CO₂ emissions reached a record 37.4 gigatons in 2023, while fossil fuel consumption remains high despite renewable energy expansion in Germany, China, and the United States.",
      "The upcoming COP30 summit in Belém, Brazil, scheduled for November 2025, will test international resolve as UN Secretary-General António Guterres urges nations to submit updated Nationally Determined Contributions with more aggressive 2035 targets."
    ],
